Next pieces of code use CSS language.
Q: button with red background and bold green text;
A:
QPushButton {background-color: red; color: green; font-weight: bold;}
Q: lines with yellow background; checkbox, buttons, combobox with red text and white background; dates with bold text;
A:
QLineEdit { background: yellow }
QCheckBox, QPushButton, QComboBox  { color: red; background-color: white }
QDateEdit { font-weight: bold; }
Q: buttons with green text and blue background;
A:
QPushButton { color: green; background-color: blue;}
Q: buttons with round orange border; disabled buttons have gray background and green text; the interface background is blue;
A:
QPushButton { border: 5px solid orange; border-radius: 10px; }
QPushButton:disabled { background-color: gray; color: green; }
QWidget { background-color: blue; }
Q: green and bold labels; the interface background is black; round buttons; pressed buttons turn green and the text italic;
A:
QLabel { color: green; font-weight: bold; font-size: 12px; }
QWidget { background-color: black; }
QPushButton { min-height: 36px; max-width: 72px; border: 2px solid; border-radius: 18px; }
QPushButton:pressed { background-color: green; font-style: italic; }
Q: red combobox with italic text; combobox text is larger at hover;
A:
QComboBox  {font-style: italic; background-color: red; }
QComboBox:pressed { font-size: 18px; }
